- Properly align query name
- Move tags to the query name row on desktop resolutions

@kocsmy please expand with more details.

### Issue Summary

Whilst in Query editor, custom parameter with type Date and Time (with seconds) works like expected, further this field is ignored when Visualization is added to any Dashboard as widget. 

### Steps to Reproduce

1. Create a query which expects data time with seconds input and chose it as Global param;
2. Run it within Query editor (execute) and you will get expected result;
3. Create a dashboard and add visualization of Query to Dashboard;

### Expected result:
- changing date param with selector would apply to particular visualization via either Dashboard Refresh or Widget refresh;

### Actual result:
- graph stays unchanged, uses param value from saved query;

### Additional debug info:
- if you alter date time Param in URL query string on open Dashboard, it will work just fine;
- if you combine this param with other params of different type (tried with drop-down), the rest of Global params except data time type will work.
- Unfortunately had n time to test with other date time options (without seconds, etc)

### Technical details:

* Redash 5.0.0-beta+b4476
* Chrome Version 67.0.3396.99 (Official Build) (64-bit):
* How did you install Redash: AWS AMI image + /bin/upgrade --channel beta

The following valid JSON results in an `Error running query: Invalid query format. The query is not a valid JSON.` error.
```
{
    "collection": "event",
    "aggregate": [
        {
            "$project": {
                "month": {
                    "$date": "$startDate"
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

